WEBVTT

00:00.554 --> 00:04.045
[♪ spooky Theremin plays ]

00:04.070 --> 00:04.870
Hey, Hank and Wanda

00:04.870 --> 00:06.205
are coming over
to my place tonight

00:06.205 --> 00:07.273
to watch scary movies.

00:07.273 --> 00:08.341
You should come too.

00:08.341 --> 00:10.209
Watching scary movies
on Halloween.

00:10.209 --> 00:12.078
That's a bit "on the nose,"
isn't it?

00:12.078 --> 00:13.145
Not really.

00:13.145 --> 00:15.548
Watching the movie
"Halloween" on Halloween,

00:15.548 --> 00:17.416
while wearing
a pointy witch's hat

00:17.416 --> 00:18.484
and a goalie mask,

00:18.484 --> 00:20.086
on Friday the 13th,

00:20.086 --> 00:20.886
that's too much.

00:21.153 --> 00:24.357
Not sure how October 31st
falls on Friday the 13th,

00:24.357 --> 00:26.225
but yeah, I'll come over.

00:26.225 --> 00:28.627
Brent, I need to
buy some insurance.

00:28.627 --> 00:31.030
Okie doke,
that'll be $20.

00:32.898 --> 00:34.233
You sell insurance?

00:34.233 --> 00:35.301
Yeah,
Halloween insurance.

00:35.301 --> 00:36.369
It's my own invention.

00:36.369 --> 00:38.237
If someone eggs or TPs

00:38.237 --> 00:39.839
or otherwise vandalizes
your property,

00:39.839 --> 00:42.241
I get it cleaned up,
no questions asked.

00:42.241 --> 00:43.309
I usually take in

00:43.309 --> 00:44.844
about 500 or 600 bucks
every year.

00:44.869 --> 00:45.953
Pretty ingenious, right?

00:45.978 --> 00:47.046
It is.

00:47.046 --> 00:47.847
You know, technically,

00:47.847 --> 00:49.715
you're turning tricks
for money on Halloween.

00:49.715 --> 00:52.118
Had to go
and make it filthy.

00:52.118 --> 00:53.452
Okay, jackass,

00:53.452 --> 00:56.122
sell me some of your
stupid rip-off

00:56.122 --> 00:57.189
Halloween insurance.

00:57.189 --> 00:58.257
Really?

00:58.257 --> 00:59.859
You've never bought
insurance from me before.

00:59.859 --> 01:02.261
All righty, then.
That'll be 60 bucks.

01:02.261 --> 01:03.329
60?!

01:03.329 --> 01:05.197
It's supposed
to be 20!

01:05.197 --> 01:06.265
20 for regular folks,

01:06.265 --> 01:08.401
who don't spend
the entire calendar year

01:08.401 --> 01:09.468
pissing people off.

01:09.468 --> 01:10.536
You're a high risk,

01:10.536 --> 01:12.405
so I need to charge
a higher premium.

01:12.405 --> 01:13.739
That's not fair!

01:13.739 --> 01:15.341
If it helps,
you can think of it

01:15.341 --> 01:18.277
as a "crusty crank
karma clause."

01:18.277 --> 01:19.321
How would that help?

01:19.345 --> 01:22.548
♪ You think
there's not a lot goin' on ♪

01:22.548 --> 01:23.883
[♪ spooky Theremin plays ]

01:23.883 --> 01:26.552
♪ Look closer, baby
you're so wrong ♪

01:26.552 --> 01:29.883
[♪♪♪]

01:32.425 --> 01:33.759
Ta-da!

01:33.759 --> 01:36.162
Behold my masterpiece!

01:36.162 --> 01:37.229
I behold,

01:37.229 --> 01:38.564
and what is it?

01:38.564 --> 01:39.632
Seriously?

01:39.632 --> 01:41.500
This is a pitch-perfect replica

01:41.500 --> 01:44.170
of Dr. Armordillo's costume.

01:44.170 --> 01:46.038
I spent months
hand-crafting it.

01:46.038 --> 01:46.572
I see,

01:46.572 --> 01:49.508
and who is Mr. Armordillo?

01:49.508 --> 01:51.377
Dr. Armordillo.

01:51.377 --> 01:54.046
He's only my favourite
comic book superhero,

01:54.046 --> 01:56.449
who didn't spend eight years
in medical school

01:56.449 --> 01:59.118
to have some rookie cop
call him "Mister."

01:59.118 --> 02:01.787
I've never heard
of your obscure nerd heroes.

02:01.787 --> 02:03.389
You never heard of Spider-Man

02:03.389 --> 02:04.457
until Tobey Maguire.

02:04.457 --> 02:07.393
I never heard of Tobey Maguire
until Spider-Man.

02:07.393 --> 02:08.727
Touché.

02:08.727 --> 02:09.795
I can't wait to put this on

02:09.795 --> 02:12.998
and patrol the town
as a real live superhero.

02:12.998 --> 02:14.308
I don't think it's fair

02:14.333 --> 02:17.536
that every year you patrol
in a fun Halloween costume,

02:17.536 --> 02:19.405
but I have to stay in uniform.

02:19.405 --> 02:21.540
It's not my fault
regulations dictate

02:21.540 --> 02:24.743
one officer must remain
in standard uniform,

02:24.743 --> 02:27.413
and this costume
took me months to build.

02:27.413 --> 02:28.747
Custom airbrushed panels,

02:28.747 --> 02:30.616
interlocking
canvas straps,

02:30.616 --> 02:31.951
hinged faceplate.

02:31.951 --> 02:34.620
I thought of everything!
[chuckling gleefully]

02:34.620 --> 02:36.755
[wailing] Oh no!

02:36.755 --> 02:39.158
Did you think
to measure yourself?

02:39.158 --> 02:41.026
How could I be so stupid?

02:41.026 --> 02:43.429
Now no one will appreciate
my artistry.

02:43.429 --> 02:45.297
I appreciate the irony.

02:45.297 --> 02:46.365
All that work,

02:46.365 --> 02:48.501
and your scales
aren't to scale?

02:48.501 --> 02:49.301
Wait.

02:49.301 --> 02:51.971
You know who
this might fit?

02:53.038 --> 02:54.907
I hate you.

02:54.907 --> 02:57.042
[♪♪♪]

02:57.042 --> 02:58.110
[doorbell ringing]

02:59.178 --> 03:00.779
Hi! Sorry, am I late?

03:00.779 --> 03:02.114
Nope, right on time.

03:02.114 --> 03:03.182
Hey, Hank.
Hey, Wanda.

03:03.182 --> 03:04.517
[yelping]

03:04.517 --> 03:06.118
Geez, you scared me.

03:06.118 --> 03:08.521
I didn't know we were
supposed to wear costumes.

03:08.521 --> 03:09.588
We're not.

03:09.588 --> 03:11.991
Hank dresses up every year
as Frankenstein.

03:11.991 --> 03:13.325
Hank-enstein.

03:13.325 --> 03:14.927
Technically,
Hankenstein's monster,

03:14.927 --> 03:17.329
but yeah, yeah,
I'm not hung up on that.

03:17.329 --> 03:18.130
What are you,

03:18.130 --> 03:19.198
some kind of
serial killer?

03:19.198 --> 03:20.266
This isn't a costume.

03:20.266 --> 03:23.202
My pressure cooker popped
while I was making ravioli.

03:23.202 --> 03:23.736
Hell of a mess.

03:24.003 --> 03:26.138
And you just decided
not to change?

03:26.138 --> 03:26.939
We're watching movies,

03:27.206 --> 03:28.807
not having crumpets
with Dame Edna.

03:28.807 --> 03:31.210
Here's the knife
I borrowed.

03:31.210 --> 03:33.078
[disembodied shriek]

03:33.078 --> 03:34.146
Ooh, spooky.

03:34.146 --> 03:36.549
Are you playing one of those
sound effect recordings?

03:36.549 --> 03:37.616
Actually, no.

03:37.616 --> 03:38.951
I'm not sure what that is.

03:38.951 --> 03:40.819
It's been happening
for the past three days.

03:40.819 --> 03:42.421
And you haven't
looked into it?

03:42.421 --> 03:45.090
Screams and such
aren't that surprising

03:45.090 --> 03:45.891
in this house.

03:45.891 --> 03:48.294
Yeah, it's got
a creepy history.

03:48.294 --> 03:49.895
History?
What history?

03:49.895 --> 03:51.230
Hey, who wants a drink?

03:51.230 --> 03:53.365
[♪♪♪]

03:53.365 --> 03:55.234
I have to go
to the bathroom.

03:55.234 --> 03:57.369
If any trick-or-treaters
come to the door,

03:57.369 --> 03:59.238
you have to dole out
the candy.

03:59.238 --> 04:00.839
And be nice!

04:00.839 --> 04:02.441
I'm always nice!

04:02.441 --> 04:04.310
[doorbell rings]

04:04.310 --> 04:06.178
Robot and a werewolf?

04:06.178 --> 04:07.513
That makes no sense.

04:07.513 --> 04:08.847
They're natural enemies.

04:08.847 --> 04:11.250
If you're going out together,
you should be a team.

04:11.250 --> 04:12.051
[slam]

04:12.051 --> 04:12.851
I don't even know

04:12.851 --> 04:14.987
what the hell
you're supposed to be.

04:14.987 --> 04:15.521
Fail!

04:15.521 --> 04:16.855
You get one piece.

04:16.855 --> 04:17.656
[slam]

04:18.991 --> 04:19.792
Hippie.

04:20.593 --> 04:22.728
How old are you, 16?

04:22.728 --> 04:25.130
And you're not even
wearing costumes,

04:25.130 --> 04:27.533
unless you're going
as a pack of jackasses.

04:27.533 --> 04:28.334
[slam]

04:28.334 --> 04:29.935
I said be nice!

04:29.935 --> 04:31.003
I'm not giving candy

04:31.003 --> 04:33.405
to a bunch of
16-year-old punks.

04:33.405 --> 04:36.342
You pissed off teenagers?

04:36.342 --> 04:37.142
On Halloween?

04:37.142 --> 04:39.812
Why don't you just paint
"Please egg our house"

04:39.812 --> 04:40.613
on the door?

04:40.613 --> 04:42.481
We're in for it now.

04:42.481 --> 04:43.816
Way to go, Oscar.

04:43.816 --> 04:46.036
I was nice
to the bug-eyed thing.

04:46.061 --> 04:47.638
[♪♪♪]

04:49.688 --> 04:51.824
[grunting stiffly]

04:51.824 --> 04:53.692
This is ridiculous.

04:53.692 --> 04:55.294
I can barely move.

04:55.294 --> 04:58.230
Dr. Armordillo
built his suit for battle,

04:58.230 --> 04:59.031
not comfort.

04:59.031 --> 05:01.700
His armor even curls
into a protective ball,

05:01.700 --> 05:03.569
like a real armadillo.

05:03.569 --> 05:04.903
The guy's a genius.

05:04.903 --> 05:07.840
A genius would've built
a costume that breathes.

05:07.840 --> 05:09.708
[grunting
and screaming in distress]

05:09.708 --> 05:10.509
I can't take it!

05:10.509 --> 05:11.577
I want out!

05:11.577 --> 05:12.645
No!

05:12.645 --> 05:13.712
I worked too hard

05:13.712 --> 05:15.848
for this costume
not to get shown off!

05:15.848 --> 05:17.716
Look, look,
I'll make you a deal.

05:17.716 --> 05:19.051
Wear this costume this year,

05:19.051 --> 05:21.720
and next year
I'll patrol in uniform,

05:21.720 --> 05:24.390
and you can dress up
as anything you want.

05:24.390 --> 05:26.258
Anything?

05:26.258 --> 05:27.593
Hmm... okay.

05:27.593 --> 05:29.194
What will I go as?

05:29.194 --> 05:31.330
Well, something slutty,
for sure,

05:31.330 --> 05:32.398
but what?

05:32.398 --> 05:33.732
Hmm...

05:33.732 --> 05:35.868
What to slut?

05:35.868 --> 05:37.736
I'm uncomfortable
with that word.

05:37.736 --> 05:38.804
Feels sexist,

05:38.804 --> 05:40.673
but you've got all year
to figure that out.

05:40.673 --> 05:43.075
Hop in,
and let's roll.

05:44.410 --> 05:46.812
[grunting stiffly]

05:46.812 --> 05:48.414
This stupid costume

05:48.414 --> 05:50.282
doesn't bend
at the waist.

05:50.282 --> 05:51.617
I can't sit down.

05:51.617 --> 05:52.685
Huh...

05:52.685 --> 05:55.087
Must've forgot
a few canvas hinges.

05:55.087 --> 05:56.155
[♪♪♪]

05:56.155 --> 05:58.023
Hey, quick question.

05:58.023 --> 06:00.159
What history
are they talking about?

06:00.159 --> 06:02.027
Oh, that history
is all bunkum,

06:02.027 --> 06:03.362
and/or hogwash.

06:03.362 --> 06:04.163
It's bunkwash.

06:04.163 --> 06:04.963
Hmm, the fact

06:05.230 --> 06:07.366
that you're using made-up words
to discount it

06:07.366 --> 06:09.234
makes me wonder if it is.

06:09.234 --> 06:09.768
It's nothing.

06:10.035 --> 06:11.637
It's just gossip
and fiddle-faddle.

06:11.637 --> 06:12.705
It's gossy-foddle.

06:12.705 --> 06:14.573
Well, let's give Lacey
the lowdown,

06:14.573 --> 06:16.175
and let her judge
for herself.

06:16.175 --> 06:17.242
Shall we?

06:17.242 --> 06:18.577
We shall.

06:18.577 --> 06:19.378
This house,

06:19.378 --> 06:20.979
the one we're in
right now,

06:20.979 --> 06:24.450
was built
by George and Julie Aberdeen.

06:24.450 --> 06:26.051
They lived here for years,

06:26.051 --> 06:27.653
but in their retirement,

06:27.653 --> 06:29.788
they took in a renter...

06:29.788 --> 06:30.856
[Wanda] They rented a room

06:30.856 --> 06:33.792
to a man
who had just moved to town.

06:33.792 --> 06:34.593
A butcher,

06:34.593 --> 06:35.928
looking for work.

06:35.928 --> 06:36.995
Lotta folks say

06:36.995 --> 06:39.398
there was something odd
about that man,

06:39.398 --> 06:41.266
and maybe there was...

06:41.266 --> 06:43.402
[Hank] ...because
soon after he moved in,

06:43.402 --> 06:45.804
the Aberdeens went missing.

06:45.804 --> 06:48.741
Butcher said they had gone
on vacation,

06:48.741 --> 06:49.808
a cruise...

06:49.808 --> 06:50.876
[Wanda]
...but folks were suspicious,

06:50.876 --> 06:54.613
because George and Julie
were always short on money.

06:54.613 --> 06:56.215
Rumours began to swirl

06:56.215 --> 06:58.884
that Butcher had locked them
in the basement crawlspace,

06:58.884 --> 07:01.019
where they starved to death.

07:01.019 --> 07:03.422
[Hank] Some say
there are fingernail marks

07:03.422 --> 07:05.023
on the crawlspace door,

07:05.023 --> 07:06.625
where they scratched in vain

07:06.625 --> 07:08.494
to get out.

07:08.494 --> 07:10.629
Okay, well,
Happy Halloween,

07:10.629 --> 07:12.231
and here's me leaving.

07:12.231 --> 07:14.633
They're just trying
to scare you.

07:14.633 --> 07:16.502
It's all a bunch
of hinkus dinkus

07:16.502 --> 07:17.035
and malarkey.

07:17.302 --> 07:18.904
Wow, you have
a lot of grampa words

07:18.904 --> 07:19.705
to discredit stuff.

07:19.705 --> 07:20.773
Hooey!

07:20.773 --> 07:21.840
No one was ever locked

07:21.840 --> 07:22.641
in the crawlspace,

07:22.641 --> 07:23.709
and I'll prove it.

07:23.709 --> 07:25.310
We'll all go down
and have a look,

07:25.310 --> 07:28.514
and we will see
exactly zero scratch marks.

07:28.514 --> 07:29.581
Awesome!

07:29.581 --> 07:30.382
Cool!

07:30.382 --> 07:32.251
Yeah, let's go
to the basement,

07:32.251 --> 07:35.454
because that's never
how a horror movie starts.

07:35.454 --> 07:37.589
[♪♪♪]

07:37.589 --> 07:39.992
Well, it took
a bit of ingenuity,

07:39.992 --> 07:41.593
but we got it figured out.

07:41.593 --> 07:42.928
[grunting]

07:42.928 --> 07:45.864
Telling me to walk
beside the car

07:45.864 --> 07:48.000
doesn't take
a lot of ingenuity.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.135
Well, you didn't
come up with it.

07:50.135 --> 07:52.004
You really think
those teenagers

07:52.004 --> 07:53.872
are going to attack
our house?

07:53.872 --> 07:54.940
How would I know?

07:54.940 --> 07:56.275
But definitely.

07:56.275 --> 07:58.677
[panting]
Rotten, no good...

07:58.677 --> 07:59.745
Relax.

07:59.745 --> 08:01.079
At the end of the day,

08:01.079 --> 08:02.948
you got Halloween insurance,

08:02.948 --> 08:05.617
so whatever happens,
Brent will clean it up.

08:05.617 --> 08:06.685
Sure.

08:06.685 --> 08:09.087
But we should still
keep a look-out.

08:09.087 --> 08:12.024
Not fair for Brent
to have to do a buncha work

08:12.024 --> 08:13.625
because of some stupid kids.

08:13.625 --> 08:16.295
It's not like you
to care about your son.

08:16.295 --> 08:17.095
How dare you?!

08:17.362 --> 08:19.765
My dear boy and I
have an unshakeable bond

08:19.765 --> 08:20.833
that could never be--

08:20.833 --> 08:22.968
You didn't buy
insurance, did you?

08:22.968 --> 08:24.837
That jerk was
ripping me off

08:24.837 --> 08:26.171
with his higher premiums

08:26.171 --> 08:27.773
and crusty karma,

08:27.773 --> 08:29.641
and I wasn't gonna
let him screw me over!

08:29.641 --> 08:32.044
Well, isn't that great?

08:32.044 --> 08:35.514
So now a gang of teenagers
will screw us instead.

08:35.514 --> 08:36.582
You're hopeless,

08:36.582 --> 08:38.183
and we're hooped.

08:39.251 --> 08:42.187
I got a bad feeling
about this.

08:42.187 --> 08:43.522
[disembodied shriek]

08:43.522 --> 08:44.590
[Hank, Wanda, and Lacey scream]

08:44.590 --> 08:46.191
Jeez, relax.

08:46.191 --> 08:48.594
Look, the lights
are still on upstairs.

08:48.594 --> 08:50.195
It's probably just a fuse.

08:50.195 --> 08:51.530
A shrieking fuse?

08:51.530 --> 08:55.000
Look, the ghost clearly
doesn't want us to be here.

08:55.000 --> 08:56.335
Say what you want
about ghosts,

08:56.335 --> 08:58.737
but they give people
plenty of warning

08:58.737 --> 08:59.538
to get out.

08:59.538 --> 09:00.339
Sometimes

09:00.339 --> 09:02.207
they even say,
"Get out!"

09:02.207 --> 09:03.275
This will only
take a second,

09:03.275 --> 09:04.610
and then we can
head back up.

09:06.745 --> 09:08.080
[they gasp in horror]

09:08.080 --> 09:09.681
Why are you gasping?

09:09.681 --> 09:11.817
There's clearly
no scratch marks.

09:11.817 --> 09:13.952
I just assumed
there would be,

09:13.952 --> 09:16.355
but you're right,
it's all smooth.

09:16.355 --> 09:17.155
Wait...

09:17.155 --> 09:19.825
The colour of the door
is different

09:19.825 --> 09:23.028
than the inside
of the crawlspace.

09:23.028 --> 09:25.163
The inside of the door
was repainted!

09:25.163 --> 09:27.032
And those hinges
look new, too.

09:27.032 --> 09:28.367
[all gasping in horror]

09:28.367 --> 09:29.434
-[doorbell rings]
-[all screaming in panic]

09:29.434 --> 09:30.235
-Who's that?

09:31.303 --> 09:33.438
Oh, it's probably
trick-or-treaters.

09:36.469 --> 09:39.030
[♪♪♪]

09:39.055 --> 09:41.414
Okay, I checked
the basement windows,

09:41.439 --> 09:42.507
and we're all locked up.

09:42.532 --> 09:44.133
So far, so good.

09:44.158 --> 09:46.027
Think again.

09:46.587 --> 09:48.989
They soaped
our living room windows?

09:48.989 --> 09:50.858
You know this
is all your fault.

09:50.858 --> 09:52.726
I know, I know!

09:52.726 --> 09:54.328
I'll get
the flashlights.

09:54.328 --> 09:56.463
Nothing else is
happening to this house!

09:56.463 --> 09:58.332
Trick or treat!

09:59.400 --> 10:02.603
This has all the elements
of a horror movie,

10:02.603 --> 10:04.738
and you're just
blindly ignoring it.

10:04.738 --> 10:07.141
Which is also an element
of every horror movie.

10:07.141 --> 10:08.208
Exactly.

10:08.208 --> 10:09.810
It happens in movies.

10:09.810 --> 10:12.212
Wanda, there's gotta be
some logical, rational,

10:12.212 --> 10:14.615
sciency explanation
for all this, right?

10:14.615 --> 10:17.017
I read that hauntings
may be manifestations

10:17.017 --> 10:18.085
of negative energies

10:18.085 --> 10:19.687
trapped in a physical space.

10:19.687 --> 10:21.555
And this is the part
where the quirky nerd

10:21.555 --> 10:23.957
explains how we
all get murdered.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.559
"Cute" quirky nerd?

10:25.559 --> 10:27.695
So the negative energies
of the Aberdeens

10:27.695 --> 10:30.097
are forever trapped
in your crawlspace.

10:30.097 --> 10:30.898
That proves it!

10:30.898 --> 10:31.965
Proves what?

10:31.965 --> 10:33.300
That someone painted a door?

10:33.300 --> 10:35.969
Can we just put
all this creepy psycho stuff

10:35.969 --> 10:36.770
behind us

10:36.795 --> 10:39.173
and go watch
"Montana Murder Ranch"?

10:39.173 --> 10:41.041
[doorbell rings]

10:42.643 --> 10:43.977
Okay, we're here.

10:43.977 --> 10:45.312
What's the emergency?

10:45.312 --> 10:46.380
We didn't
call the cops.

10:46.380 --> 10:47.448
Maybe you didn't.

10:47.448 --> 10:49.049
What took you
so long?

10:49.049 --> 10:49.850
And where's Karen?

10:49.850 --> 10:51.185
Karen is, uh...

10:51.185 --> 10:53.053
bringing up
the rear.

10:53.053 --> 10:55.189
[grunting awkwardly]

10:55.189 --> 10:56.790
Who are you
supposed to be?

10:56.790 --> 10:59.727
Professor Possum,
or Admiral Aardvark.

10:59.727 --> 11:01.328
You ever
heard of him?

11:01.328 --> 11:02.663
Exactly.

11:02.663 --> 11:04.531
You ever hear of
Spider-Man?

11:04.531 --> 11:05.332
Of course.

11:05.332 --> 11:08.001
Yeah, well... still.

11:08.001 --> 11:09.336
[grunting awkwardly]

11:09.336 --> 11:10.938
I pissed off
some Halloweeners,

11:10.938 --> 11:13.340
and now
they're out for blood.

11:13.340 --> 11:14.408
I want police
protection.

11:14.408 --> 11:15.476
Protection?

11:15.476 --> 11:17.611
What are a few
kids gonna do?

11:17.611 --> 11:19.213
It wasn't
little kids.

11:19.213 --> 11:20.814
It was teenagers.

11:20.814 --> 11:23.217
You pissed off teenagers?

11:23.217 --> 11:23.751
Oh, no.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.619
They're the worst kind
of 'agers.

11:25.619 --> 11:26.687
I know.

11:26.687 --> 11:28.555
They've already
soaped our windows.

11:28.555 --> 11:30.691
God only knows
what they'll do next.

11:30.691 --> 11:31.759
I'll radio Karen

11:31.759 --> 11:33.093
to secure
the perimeter.

11:33.093 --> 11:34.428
You two, stay sharp.

11:34.428 --> 11:35.763
I'll go look
for teenagers

11:35.763 --> 11:37.364
with soapy hands.

11:37.364 --> 11:38.165
[♪♪♪]

11:40.033 --> 11:42.436
Now, if you don't want
"Montana Murder Ranch,"

11:42.436 --> 11:44.838
there's also "Texas
Bloodbath Blitz,"

11:44.838 --> 11:46.707
"The Lone Star
Slaughter,"

11:46.707 --> 11:49.109
or "Terror on
Tumbleweed Trail."

11:49.109 --> 11:51.512
Boy, we've got a real
western theme going here.

11:51.512 --> 11:52.579
What I want to know is,

11:52.579 --> 11:53.914
who owned this house

11:53.914 --> 11:56.049
after the Aberdeens'
demise?

11:56.049 --> 11:56.850
That's the thing.

11:57.117 --> 11:59.520
After the Aberdeens
died in the basement,

11:59.520 --> 12:02.189
the Butcher conveniently
produced a document

12:02.189 --> 12:04.324
that transferred
the title to him.

12:04.324 --> 12:04.858
Nobody died

12:04.858 --> 12:06.727
or demised
in my basement.

12:06.727 --> 12:08.862
In the months that followed,

12:08.862 --> 12:11.799
more people from town
went missing.

12:11.799 --> 12:13.400
Okay, you're
freaking me out.

12:13.400 --> 12:14.735
That's 'cause
she's bottom-lit

12:14.735 --> 12:15.803
by her phone.

12:15.803 --> 12:18.472
Oh, it's
a notification.

12:18.472 --> 12:19.807
Hot Singles
in My Area.

12:19.807 --> 12:21.408
[chuckling]
Talk about fake news.

12:21.408 --> 12:22.476
Anyway...

12:22.476 --> 12:24.077
Rumours
started to swirl

12:24.077 --> 12:25.679
about there being
a locked freezer

12:25.679 --> 12:27.014
in the garage.

12:27.014 --> 12:29.149
There's nothing wrong
with a locked freezer.

12:29.149 --> 12:29.950
Meat is valuable.

12:30.217 --> 12:32.619
Is it so hard to believe
people might steal steaks?

12:32.619 --> 12:35.556
Or that people
might become steaks!

12:36.356 --> 12:37.157
Anyway,

12:37.157 --> 12:37.958
one day,

12:38.225 --> 12:40.894
the police went to confront
the Butcher,

12:40.894 --> 12:42.763
but he'd left town,

12:42.763 --> 12:43.564
and...

12:43.564 --> 12:45.699
he took his freezer with him.

12:45.699 --> 12:47.835
Full of human steaks?

12:47.835 --> 12:50.237
Some say there's still
a blood stain on the floor

12:50.237 --> 12:51.839
where the freezer
used to be.

12:51.839 --> 12:52.906
Who are these
"some people"

12:52.906 --> 12:54.241
who say
all these things?

12:54.241 --> 12:57.444
Some say they were
residents of the town.

12:57.444 --> 12:59.046
Okay.

13:00.380 --> 13:01.715
[owl hoots softly]

13:03.050 --> 13:04.651
[twig snaps]

13:04.651 --> 13:05.719
[creature snarls]

13:05.719 --> 13:07.588
Who's there?

13:08.375 --> 13:10.524
Stupid piece of junk!

13:10.524 --> 13:11.859
Ah, finally.

13:13.727 --> 13:14.528
[yelping]

13:14.528 --> 13:16.129
[screaming]

13:16.129 --> 13:16.663
Emma!

13:16.663 --> 13:19.066
There's a demon in the garden!

13:21.735 --> 13:22.803
What the...

13:22.803 --> 13:24.938
Karen, you're supposed to be
at Oscar and Emma's,

13:24.938 --> 13:26.540
but you're trick or treating?

13:26.540 --> 13:28.408
Look, I get that you're angry,

13:28.408 --> 13:30.277
but acting out like this?

13:30.277 --> 13:31.612
Pretty unprofessional.

13:31.612 --> 13:33.480
[cell phone rings]

13:33.480 --> 13:34.548
DRPD.

13:34.548 --> 13:35.616
[Oscar] Davis!

13:35.616 --> 13:36.950
The teen demons are here!

13:36.950 --> 13:38.819
There's children in the corn!

13:38.819 --> 13:40.420
[beeps off phone]
Teens are attacking.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.022
We gotta go.

13:44.958 --> 13:47.628
Fine, I'll
carry you.

13:47.628 --> 13:48.428
[grunting]

13:50.564 --> 13:52.699
[♪♪♪]

13:52.699 --> 13:53.767
Have a look for yourselves.

13:53.767 --> 13:56.436
There are no stains
on the floor.

13:56.436 --> 13:57.504
There's a stain.

13:57.504 --> 13:58.572
Okay, that's oil.

13:58.572 --> 13:59.907
There's a stain.

13:59.907 --> 14:01.508
That one's
anti-freeze,

14:01.508 --> 14:03.110
and that one over there
is mustard.

14:03.110 --> 14:05.779
Sometimes I barbecue hot dogs
in here in the winter.

14:05.779 --> 14:06.580
Huh.

14:06.580 --> 14:07.915
There isn't a single crack.

14:07.915 --> 14:10.584
Highly irregular
for concrete from the '50s,

14:10.584 --> 14:11.919
wouldn't you say?

14:11.919 --> 14:12.986
What are you,
a concrete maven?

14:12.986 --> 14:14.054
When concrete
is poured,

14:14.054 --> 14:16.723
the company often presses
a date stamp into it.

14:16.723 --> 14:17.524
A-ha!

14:17.524 --> 14:19.393
1985.

14:19.393 --> 14:20.460
So it is new.

14:20.460 --> 14:22.062
Nice try, floor,

14:22.062 --> 14:23.931
you lying
slab of stains!

14:23.931 --> 14:25.799
-[doorbell rings]
-[they all scream]

14:25.799 --> 14:28.468
How many kids
are in this town?

14:28.468 --> 14:30.070
A demon teen?

14:30.070 --> 14:31.939
You have to be
more specific.

14:31.939 --> 14:33.540
That could be
any one of them.

14:33.540 --> 14:34.341
It had claws

14:34.341 --> 14:36.209
and beady
red eyes, and--

14:36.209 --> 14:37.544
And it was me.

14:37.544 --> 14:38.879
Karen?

14:38.879 --> 14:40.747
You're supposed
to be over there.

14:40.747 --> 14:42.616
Wait, if you're Karen,

14:42.616 --> 14:43.951
then...

14:44.751 --> 14:45.819
My name's Kenny.

14:45.819 --> 14:47.955
Two Dr. Armordillos?

14:47.955 --> 14:48.755
See, Karen?

14:48.755 --> 14:50.090
I told you
he was popular.

14:50.090 --> 14:51.158
Can we get back

14:51.158 --> 14:52.225
to the pimply
terrorists

14:52.225 --> 14:54.361
who are trying to
destroy my house?

14:54.361 --> 14:55.696
[cell phone rings]

14:55.696 --> 14:57.297
DRPD.

14:57.297 --> 14:58.098
Uh-huh.

14:58.098 --> 14:59.433
Missing child...

14:59.433 --> 15:00.233
Uh-oh.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.636
Dressed like a
scaly rat dentist.

15:02.636 --> 15:03.704
He's a doctor.

15:03.704 --> 15:04.771
Got it.

15:04.771 --> 15:05.839
We'll keep
a look-out.

15:05.839 --> 15:07.975
Kenny,
this was a test

15:07.975 --> 15:09.576
to see if you'd
trust strangers,

15:09.576 --> 15:11.178
and you failed
miserably.

15:11.178 --> 15:13.313
Leave the candy
and run along.

15:14.381 --> 15:15.716
Oh, look.

15:15.716 --> 15:17.584
His knees can bend.

15:17.584 --> 15:18.919
Be that as it may,

15:18.919 --> 15:19.987
it's been
a good night.

15:19.987 --> 15:21.054
We found a lost kid,

15:21.054 --> 15:22.122
scored some candy,

15:22.122 --> 15:24.257
and prevented
more vandalism.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.325
Not so fast.

15:26.393 --> 15:28.795
[Emma] Well, thank god
we have Halloween insurance.

15:28.795 --> 15:30.931
Oh, right...

15:30.931 --> 15:32.265
we don't.

15:35.702 --> 15:37.571
[♪♪♪]

15:37.571 --> 15:40.774
That is a lot
of toilet paper.

15:40.774 --> 15:42.109
Two ply.

15:42.109 --> 15:42.909
[tasting]

15:42.909 --> 15:44.244
High-grade stuff.

15:44.244 --> 15:45.846
Davis,
take señor rat

15:45.846 --> 15:48.248
and go arrest
every teenager in town.

15:48.248 --> 15:49.583
If you arrest
the teens,

15:49.583 --> 15:51.451
you just make them
more angry.

15:51.451 --> 15:53.320
Look, the longer
we stand here,

15:53.320 --> 15:53.854
the more time

15:54.121 --> 15:55.722
the rest of the house
is exposed.

15:55.722 --> 15:58.392
Everyone, take a side
and protect it.

15:59.993 --> 16:02.129
[walls and floors creaking]

16:02.129 --> 16:02.929
[distant thud]

16:02.929 --> 16:05.599
Look, it doesn't
take science

16:05.599 --> 16:08.001
to know that Brent's house
is being haunted

16:08.001 --> 16:09.870
by the ghosts
of the Aberdeens.

16:09.870 --> 16:10.937
[Brent] Wrong.

16:10.937 --> 16:12.539
I googled
their obituaries.

16:12.539 --> 16:15.475
They died on
a Mediterranean cruise.

16:15.475 --> 16:16.543
That's tragic,

16:16.543 --> 16:18.145
but for
my purposes here--

16:18.145 --> 16:18.945
A-ha!

16:18.945 --> 16:21.348
Then your house
is being haunted by...

16:21.348 --> 16:22.949
the Butcher.

16:22.949 --> 16:24.017
How is he haunting me?

16:24.017 --> 16:25.886
It's the Aberdeens
that died,

16:25.886 --> 16:26.953
and it doesn't help

16:26.953 --> 16:28.555
that you keep calling him
"The Butcher."

16:28.555 --> 16:30.690
He's got a name.
It's Murray.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.025
Here we go.
I found him.

16:32.025 --> 16:33.360
Murray Butcher.

16:33.360 --> 16:34.694
He moved to Stonewood.

16:34.694 --> 16:36.563
Opened Butcher's
Butcher Shop.

16:36.563 --> 16:38.698
Okay, that's
on the nose.

16:38.698 --> 16:39.766
He ran it
for 20 years,

16:39.766 --> 16:40.567
then retired.

16:40.567 --> 16:41.635
End of story.

16:41.635 --> 16:43.236
And then he died.

16:43.236 --> 16:44.037
Oh.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.906
Three days ago.

16:46.973 --> 16:48.308
How long did you say

16:48.308 --> 16:51.511
your house was making
weird noises?

16:51.511 --> 16:52.579
I can't remember.

16:52.579 --> 16:53.914
You said
it was three--

16:53.914 --> 16:56.049
It was
three days.

16:57.651 --> 16:58.985
Ouch!

16:58.985 --> 17:00.320
Hey!

17:00.320 --> 17:01.388
Sorry about that.

17:01.388 --> 17:02.722
Thought you were
a teen.

17:02.722 --> 17:04.591
Got a little
trigger-happy.

17:04.591 --> 17:06.460
It's too dark to
find rocks to throw.

17:06.460 --> 17:07.794
Anything
going on here?

17:07.794 --> 17:08.595
Nothing.

17:08.595 --> 17:10.197
All is quiet.

17:10.197 --> 17:12.065
Almost... too quiet.

17:12.065 --> 17:12.866
Nope.

17:12.866 --> 17:13.934
Just about
the right amount.

17:13.934 --> 17:15.535
[Karen, over radio]
Davis, are you there?

17:15.535 --> 17:16.336
Roger.

17:16.336 --> 17:18.472
Sorry, Roger,
can I talk to Davis?

17:18.472 --> 17:21.141
[cackling]
I love that gag.

17:21.141 --> 17:22.209
I hate that gag.

17:22.209 --> 17:23.276
You see anything?

17:23.276 --> 17:24.878
I saw something,

17:24.878 --> 17:26.746
and I caught something.

17:26.746 --> 17:28.615
[suspenseful music flourish]

17:28.615 --> 17:30.750
[disembodied shriek]

17:30.750 --> 17:32.085
Okay, so

17:32.085 --> 17:35.822
I think that now
we can all agree

17:35.822 --> 17:38.758
there is a ghost
in Brent's house.

17:38.758 --> 17:40.360
I emphatically
disagree.

17:40.360 --> 17:41.161
Brent's right.

17:41.161 --> 17:42.496
It could very well be

17:42.496 --> 17:44.898
some other evil,
undead entity.

17:44.898 --> 17:45.966
We should cover
all our bases.

17:45.966 --> 17:48.902
Get some holy water,
garlic, wooden stakes.

17:48.902 --> 17:49.970
What if
it's a werewolf?

17:49.970 --> 17:51.037
Oh, good point.

17:51.037 --> 17:52.372
Lacey, go melt
your earrings.

17:52.372 --> 17:54.241
Wanda, go find
Brent's bullet-maker.

17:54.241 --> 17:55.041
We don't
necessarily

17:55.041 --> 17:56.643
have to fight
this thing.

17:56.643 --> 17:58.778
We could try
reasoning with it.

17:58.778 --> 18:00.914
Brent, where's
your Ouija board?

18:00.914 --> 18:01.982
It's in the cloakroom

18:01.982 --> 18:03.583
with my crossbow
and crystals.

18:03.583 --> 18:05.452
This is no time
to make jokes.

18:05.452 --> 18:06.786
The one
who makes jokes

18:06.786 --> 18:07.854
usually dies first.

18:07.854 --> 18:09.723
I thought
it was the virgin.

18:09.723 --> 18:11.591
Any last words,
Hank?

18:11.591 --> 18:12.392
Uh...

18:12.392 --> 18:14.528
maybe we could conjure up
a bigger ghost

18:14.528 --> 18:15.862
to punch this one out.

18:15.862 --> 18:17.197
Lacey,
hop on the Ouija

18:17.197 --> 18:18.798
and dial up
Andre The Giant.

18:18.798 --> 18:21.468
Everyone take a breath
and come back to Earth.

18:21.468 --> 18:23.336
We're here to have some fun

18:23.336 --> 18:24.671
and watch a movie,

18:24.671 --> 18:25.739
so let's do that.

18:25.739 --> 18:27.340
Here's one.

18:27.340 --> 18:29.743
"The Basement Butcher
of Bog Hollow."

18:29.743 --> 18:31.344
It's very thematic.

18:31.344 --> 18:31.878
Can't do it.

18:31.878 --> 18:33.480
-Nope.
-I'm out.

18:33.480 --> 18:35.882
[♪♪♪]

18:35.882 --> 18:38.018
Those little bastards
egged the house!

18:38.018 --> 18:39.886
Karen, where are
the perps?

18:39.886 --> 18:41.755
The perps
are right here.

18:41.755 --> 18:42.822
Emma's the one

18:42.822 --> 18:44.157
who's been
trashing the house.

18:44.157 --> 18:46.826
The metal in that costume
has leaked into her brain.

18:46.826 --> 18:47.894
It's fiberglass.

18:47.894 --> 18:50.564
Each piece
lovingly hand-crafted.

18:50.564 --> 18:51.898
I got suspicious

18:51.898 --> 18:53.500
because she always
seemed to be missing

18:53.500 --> 18:54.568
from the group

18:54.568 --> 18:56.436
when the vandals struck...

18:56.436 --> 18:59.639
[Karen] So, when she
told everyone to spread out,

18:59.639 --> 19:01.775
I kept my eye on her.

19:01.775 --> 19:03.109
I found a button on the costume

19:03.109 --> 19:05.779
that helped me go undercover.

19:05.779 --> 19:07.647
[muffled yelp]

19:07.647 --> 19:08.715
[Karen] Sort of.

19:08.715 --> 19:12.452
Anyway, that's when I saw Emma
throwing eggs

19:12.452 --> 19:14.113
at her own house!

19:17.791 --> 19:19.125
Fine,
I admit it.

19:19.125 --> 19:20.994
I would've gotten away
with it, too,

19:20.994 --> 19:23.396
if it wasn't for this
masked meddler!

19:23.396 --> 19:26.066
Usually the one in the mask
gets caught by meddling--

19:26.066 --> 19:27.667
Well, you've all seen
Scooby-Doo,

19:27.667 --> 19:29.002
you know
how it plays out.

19:29.002 --> 19:30.604
You've been
on me all night

19:30.604 --> 19:31.938
about not getting
insurance,

19:31.938 --> 19:34.074
and then you go and
vandalize our own home?

19:34.074 --> 19:34.874
Why?

19:34.874 --> 19:37.811
Because I bought
Halloween insurance.

19:37.811 --> 19:39.679
I knew you would be
too cheap,

19:39.679 --> 19:41.548
so I bought it myself,

19:41.548 --> 19:42.882
and since we were covered,

19:42.882 --> 19:45.018
I took the opportunity
to mess with you

19:45.018 --> 19:46.886
and pretend teens
were attacking the house.

19:46.886 --> 19:49.823
So Brent has to
clean this up after all?

19:49.823 --> 19:51.157
[chuckling] Well...

19:51.157 --> 19:53.026
let's make it
good and messy, then!

19:53.026 --> 19:54.894
[laughing gleefully]

19:54.894 --> 19:55.695
H'yah!

19:55.695 --> 19:57.030
[cackling]

19:57.030 --> 19:58.098
[eggs splatting]

19:58.098 --> 19:59.432
[laughing]

19:59.432 --> 20:02.636
[rowdy cheering]

20:03.436 --> 20:04.771
Bye!

20:04.771 --> 20:06.373
Have a terrific evening!

20:06.373 --> 20:09.042
I'll stay here alone
with the crazy killer ghost

20:09.042 --> 20:11.177
that I'm not afraid of!

20:11.978 --> 20:14.114
[snarling shriek nearby]

20:14.114 --> 20:15.448
[screaming in terror]

20:15.448 --> 20:17.851
Y-you guys, wait!

20:19.452 --> 20:21.054
[chittering]

20:21.054 --> 20:22.922
[snarling shriek]

20:22.922 --> 20:25.592
Takes a shocking
and keeps on gnawing.

20:25.592 --> 20:27.727
Well, I guess
the mystery is solved.

20:27.727 --> 20:28.528
Yep.

20:28.528 --> 20:29.596
The raccoons
are possessed

20:29.596 --> 20:31.197
by the ghost
of Murray Butcher.

20:31.197 --> 20:34.134
I can't believe
you're scared of raccoons.

20:34.134 --> 20:36.002
Cute, furry little--

20:36.002 --> 20:37.070
[snarling shriek]

20:37.070 --> 20:38.672
[all screaming in panic]

20:38.672 --> 20:39.739
[♪♪♪]

20:41.605 --> 20:44.277
[♪♪♪]

20:44.277 --> 20:45.612
What a mess.

20:45.612 --> 20:46.680
Geez, I was right

20:46.680 --> 20:48.548
when I said you were
a high-risk case.

20:48.548 --> 20:50.417
You better get busy.

20:50.417 --> 20:51.751
There's lots
to clean up.

20:51.751 --> 20:53.620
Yep. We'll get on it
right away.

20:53.620 --> 20:54.954
"We'll"
get on it?

20:54.954 --> 20:57.090
I always subcontract
the cleaning to teenagers.

20:57.090 --> 20:59.759
Cheap labour,
and I pocket the difference.

20:59.759 --> 21:02.429
[grumbling]
I hate kids.

21:02.429 --> 21:03.496
Especially our own.

21:03.496 --> 21:07.767
[♪♪♪]

21:07.767 --> 21:09.636
♪ I don't know

21:09.636 --> 21:12.038
♪ The same things
you don't know ♪

21:15.508 --> 21:17.377
♪ I don't know

21:17.377 --> 21:19.779
♪ I just... don't know

21:22.716 --> 21:25.118
♪ Ooh...

21:25.118 --> 21:26.720
♪ It's a great big place

21:26.720 --> 21:28.855
♪ Ooh...

21:28.855 --> 21:30.457
♪ Full of nothin' but space

21:30.457 --> 21:32.592
♪ Ooh...

21:32.592 --> 21:34.437
♪ And it's my happy place

21:34.462 --> 21:36.597
♪ I don't know ♪
